Package graph

Interface TopologicalSort<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of object in this graph.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Graph<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TopoSort
    public interface TopologicalSort<T>
extends Graph<T>
    Do a topological sort on a graph. Note: A TopologicalSort object is a Graph, so it sorts itself. There is no need to "provide" the TopologcialSort with a graph.

    • Method Detail

      • getSort

        java.util.List<T> getSort()
                   throws GraphError
        Do a topological sort on this graph, if it is acyclic. A topological sort is a listing of the nodes in the (acyclic) graph such that if there is a path in the graph from node A to node B then node A will appear before node B in the listing.
        Returns:
        a topological sort of this graph
        Throws:
        GraphError - if the graph is not acyclic
